Description: Landscape with St. Catherine, Washington. Clearly connected with Wellens de Cock-Matthys Cock-Master of Errera-Sketchbookgroup: see illustration in K.G. Boon, 'De tekenaar van het Errera-schetsboek', Bulletin Musée R. 1955, 1-3, pp. 215ff. The background scene with the wheel painted in Bosch technique. The group of figures originally in the picture also rather Bosch-like. Closest not to the Jan Wellens de Cock (?). Boston (Boon, fig. 5), but to the formerly with Benedict (fig.4).
